            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Simone Moreau\u2019s aesthetic was born in the humid, vibrant streets of New Orleans. Raised in a proud Creole family in the Trem\u00e9 neighborhood, her childhood was a sensory feast of wrought-iron balconies, the mournful brass of a distant jazz funeral, and the rich textures of her grandmother\u2019s sewing room. This environment fueled her path to a Bachelor's in Fine Arts, where she excelled in sculpture and textile arts, though she graduated with little idea of how to translate her passion into a stable living.\n\nHer turning point came during a post-college trip to San Francisco in her early twenties. Captivated by the city\u2019s kinetic energy and creative spirit, she decided to stay, trading the languid pace of the South for the fog and ambition of the West Coast. She took a low-paying job dressing windows for a small boutique in Hayes Valley, where her innate talent for composition and storytelling through objects blossomed. She discovered the practical magic of visual merchandising\u2014art with a commercial purpose.\n\nSimone\u2019s career was a steady, two-decade ascent through the ranks of retail. She parlayed her skills into roles at larger department stores, learning the business of desire, foot traffic, and brand identity. Now, as a Visual Merchandising Director for a major apparel brand, she manages teams and shapes the in-store experience across the region.\n\nToday, Simone lives alone in a tastefully curated apartment in the Mission, not far from where her SF journey began. Her 3.8-mile Muni ride to her FiDi office is a daily ritual of observation, where she sketches ideas in a small notebook. Though currently single, her life is filled with a chosen family of fellow creatives\u2014a chef, a graphic designer, and a writer\u2014with whom she shares wine-fueled dinners and gallery openings. She loves San Francisco for its blend of grit and polish, finding inspiration in everything from the murals on Clarion Alley to the elegant displays at SFMOMA.\n\nLately, the corporate grind has begun to wear on her. Simone dreams of cashing in her hard-won stability for a new venture: her own small concept store, a space blending art, design, and community, a true reflection of the girl from New Orleans who learned to build worlds within four walls."
